news.title: PE investment in Indian real estate rise 6% to $2.82 billion in April-December 2024: Anarock
news.para: In the April to December FY25, the industrial and logistics sector captured 62% of total investments, significantly surpassing both the office and residential sectors, which attracted 14% and 15%.

news.title: State government in talks with railways and centre for metro: Goa CM
news.para: The  chief minister Pramod Sawant also said that there are already 50 to 60 IT companies operating in Goa and that the state is thinking of creating an IT hub too in the state.

news.title: Delhi LG reviews progress of Noida international airport
news.para: Delhi's Lieutenant Governor (LG) Vinai Kumar Saxena also praised the Uttar Pradesh govt for the rapid development of the airport within a short timeframe.

news.title: MPMRCL's MD inspects Bhopal metro project works
news.para: It including the Subhash Nagar Depot, to assess construction progress and coordinate officials, consultants, and contractors for the July passenger operations launch.

news.title: Spain government announces new measures to tackle housing crisis
news.para: The 12 announcements aim to offer more social housing, improve regulation and provide more support to renters, Socialist Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez told an economic forum in Madrid.

news.title: Country Garden's property services arm predicts $150.03 million earnings drop
news.para: The unit, Country Garden Services, said the impairment was primarily because the expansion of its sanitation business had not been carried out as was scheduled and expected in the past years, leading to a drop in both sales and profit.

news.title: SBB's creditor Fir Tree Partners drops lawsuit
news.para: Fir Tree has since 2023 sought immediate debt repayment from SBB, citing what it said was a breach of a bond clause, a claim rejected by the Swedish group.

news.title: MADC starts razing structures in Shivangaon for airport expansion
news.para: While many villagers shifted to the new place, several others continued to stay in the village. Some even rented out their dwelling units or allowed their kin to live in their place in Shivangaon.

news.title: Lucknow development body razes illegal construction on nazul land
news.para: LDA officials said the encroachers failed to comply despite repeated warnings to vacate the area. Subsequently, LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar instructed the LDA team to carry out a drive to remove the encroachments.

news.title: Kolkata: Police commissioner directs OCs to ensure no encroachment of government land
news.para: The order stated that necessary coordination with authorities of civil administration, like KMC and other agencies, should be made to identify vacant govt land.

news.title: Patna civic body starts drive against property tax defaulters
news.para: The authorities have scheduled two rounds for seizure operations, with enforcement measures planned against non-compliant property owners.

news.title: Mysuru civic body’s e-khata drive boosts revenue by Rs 1.7 crore in December 2024
news.para: To receive e-khatas, applicants must clear all their pending property tax and water cess dues from the last five years.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to mop up Rs 30 crore water dues
news.para: So far, only Rs 38 crore out of the targeted Rs 68 crore (55%) has been collected. Over 270 major defaulters—spanning industrial, institutional, group housing, and commercial categories—whose dues are above Rs 50,000 have recently been issued notices.

news.title: Rajasthan government orders 100% rebate on UD tax interest filed before March 31
news.para: Similarly, on lump sum payment of pending UD tax from cases before 2011-12, along with the exemption of penalty, a 50% discount on the principal has also been given.

news.title: Noida International airport to launch in four months but connectivity remains a concern
news.para: Jewar, where the airport is located, is around 90km from IGI Airport in Delhi, 70km from Connaught Place, 60km from Noida City Centre and 40km from Pari Chowk in Greater Noida, the last point on the metro grid.

news.title: About 90% defaulters yet to clear Rs 317 crore power dues in Noida
news.para: While the said consumers are of the first phase, clearing Rs 30.40 crore dues out of a total of Rs 347 crore, officials maintain strict implementation of the OTS scheme henceforth.

news.title: Mangaluru’s IT park project stuck in DPR stage
news.para: Karnataka State Electronics Development Corporation Limited (KEONICS) obtained govt approval for developing an IT park spanning over 3.2 acres at Derebail through a public-private partnership (PPP).

news.title: CIDCO's conditions on buyers to be relaxed, prices to be lowered: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Speaking to a regional news channel, the state minister for social justice said the current rules prevent a person from buying a property built by CIDCO if his father already owns one.

news.title: JSW Cement gets Sebi's approval to raise Rs 4,000 crore through IPO
news.para: The initial share sale comprises a fresh issue of equity shares worth Rs 2,000 crore and an Offer-for-Sale (OFS) of Rs 2,000 crore by investor shareholders, according to the Draft Red Herring Prospectus (DRHP) filed in August last year.

news.title: China Evergrande's unit receives liquidation order from Hong Kong court
news.para: The liquidators had filed a winding-up petition against company subsidiary CEG Holdings BVI in September, in a bid to recover funds from the debt-laden property company that defaulted in 2021 and triggered China's real estate market crisis.
